750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*77UZWGWM_aWdu8FszVqvuQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*77UZWGWM_aWdu8FszVqvuQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*77UZWGWM_aWdu8FszVqvuQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*77UZWGWM_aWdu8FszVqvuQ.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*77UZWGWM_aWdu8FszVqvuQ.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">The function here is x² and taking its integral with the limits from 2 to 3 gives us the area shaded in blue.</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
